<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="192" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2369.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Luis Mena, Nicaraguan revolutionist, has been reported at Central
                            Sugar Company, Guantanamo, until November 23. It is stated that General
                            Mena left Cuba for Costa Rica for the purpose of starting revolutionary
                            activity against Government of Nicaragua. Request Cuban Government to
                            furnish you with all information obtainable regarding his movements.
                            Report by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>